 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Standard Import tool demonstration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 38,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os, json\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import notebook_startup\n",
    "from libcbm.input.sit import sit_cbm_factory\n",
    "from libcbm.model.cbm import cbm_simulator"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup\n",
    "Load the standard import tool configuration at the specified path.  This configuration encompasses the data source for the various sit inputs (sit_inventory, sit_classifiers etc.) and also the relationships of classifiers, and disturbance types to the default CBM parameters."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "config_path = os.path.abspath(\"./sit/growth_only/sit_config.json\")\n",
    "sit = sit_cbm_factory.load_sit(config_path)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Initialize and validate the inventory in the sit dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 41,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "classifiers, inventory = sit_cbm_factory.initialize_inventory(sit)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Initialize an instance of the CBM model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 42,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cbm = sit_cbm_factory.initialize_cbm(sit)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Create storage and a function for storing CBM simulation results.  This particular implementation appends timestep results for each step into a running DataFrame which is stored in memory."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 43,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results, reporting_func = cbm_simulator.create_in_memory_reporting_func()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Simulation\n",
    "The following line of code spins up the CBM inventory and runs it through 100 timesteps. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 44,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cbm_simulator.simulate(\n",
    "    cbm, \n",
    "    n_steps=1000,\n",
    "    classifiers=classifiers,\n",
    "    inventory=inventory, \n",
    "    pool_codes=sit.defaults.get_pools(), \n",
    "    flux_indicator_codes=sit.defaults.get_flux_indicators(), \n",
    "    pre_dynamics_func = lambda x: x,\n",
    "    reporting_func=reporting_func)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
